{\par \b Syntax:}\par MOUSE[(index)]\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the current pointer&#39;s location.\par returns: two  lists of the form \{#x, #y, #originalx, #originaly, #type\}, one for each potential pointer. \par Note, if a pointer is unused, returns an empty list\par #type is:  #0: New, #1: Completed, #2: Drag, #3: Stretch, #4: Rotate, #5: LongClick\par \par MOUSE(x) returns the nth element that would be returned if MOUSE was called with no arguements or -1 if the associated pointer is not down.\par
